qUnd: Not really, no.  It seemed that though you start by selecting all 3 nodes of level one and determine the highest value, you could still end up with a low value on level 2.  The previous level does not indicate that the following level with hold a high value. It is random and following the diagram does not guarantee a high value.
qDes: Click the unobserved nodes on level one. From there, determine which node has the highest value and then click the corresponding node on level two.  If a high number, continue by selecting a node on level 3 which seems more like a 50/50 chance of guessing a high number. Or you could simply click all the nodes to see which route gains you the highest value.

I remember the first question on that page about understanding the flowchart directions and would like to answer it as follows: I was unclear about whether the phrase "highest level of the tree" referred to the absolute top level/level 3 or to the highest available level. When completing the tree task, I interpreted the directions as referring to the top tree level/level 3. I thus only clicked to reveal money values on level 3 of the tree. I hope I interpreted the instructions correctly so as not to interfere with your data collection.
